<div2>                
<lg>                <head>WHAT IS CHRISTMAS?</head> 

<figure><figDesc>Christmas Tree</figDesc></figure>
                
<lg>
<l>This holiest of all the nights,</l>                             
<l>I wonder what it means?</l>                                     
<l>It's surely more than candlelights</l>                          
<l>On tinselled evergreens.</l>                                    
<l>It's more than toys that make it dear</l>                       
<l>And eating pleasant things, </l>                                 
<l>For if you listen right you'll hear </l>                        
<l>A murmuring of wings.</l>
 </lg>                                   
                
<lg>
<l>My grandma says its more than fun</l>         
<l>And hanging up your stocking.</l>
<l>It's knowing any needy one</l>
<l>Might be the Savior knocking.</l>
<l>It's helping those who feel the rod</l>
<l>Of grief and heavy labors.</l> 
<l>I guess its being nice to God</l>
<l>By loving all your neighbors</l></lg>

<byline>by John Neihardt</byline></lg>
        </div2>        
                
          <pb facs="nei.j4c.22.30-31_0002"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">31</fw>
                <note type="curatorial">30-1</note>
                
<div2>
              <opener>  
                  <dateline>
                Skyrim<lb/>
                
                Xmas, 1958
                  </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Stewart:</salute>
              </opener>
                <p>Here's a little present. I'm sure you will know how to use it. <hi rend="underline">And don't overlook the affection it carries from</hi></p>
              <closer>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Gaki Neihardt</hi></signed>
              </closer>
                     
             </div2> 
            </div1>
